BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Shakespeare Out of a Hat: Romeo and Juliet
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20270225T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20270225T204500
DTSTAMP:20260714T211456Z
UID:occ-1528@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Improv Comedy
DESCRIPTION:Romeo and Juliet with roles drawn from a hat two minutes befor
 e curtain — and a happy ending.\n\nThe play is set\, but the casting isn
 't: the Atlanta Shakespeare Company's actors pull their roles out of a hat
  moments before the show starts\, so nobody knows who's playing Romeo\, Ju
 liet\, or the Nurse until it's underway. Part improv\, part Shakespeare\, 
 and this version promises the star-crossed lovers a happy ending. A one-ni
 ght-only special event\, performed with the company's usual table seating 
 and food and drink service.
GEO:33.768171;-84.3851523
LAST-MODIFIED:20260714T161552Z
LOCATION:Shakespeare Tavern Playhouse\, 499 Peachtree St NE
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://www.shakespearetavern.com/on-stage/company/shakespeare-out-of-
 a-hat-romeo-and-juliet-one-night-only
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Shakespeare Out of a Hat: Julius Caesar
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20270315T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20270315T204500
DTSTAMP:20260714T211456Z
UID:occ-1542@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Improv Comedy
DESCRIPTION:Improv meets Shakespeare: actors draw their Julius Caesar role
 s from a hat two minutes before the show begins.\n\nThe Atlanta Shakespear
 e Company's classically trained actors know the script\; nobody knows who'
 s playing whom until roles come out of a hat moments before curtain. The p
 lay in question is Julius Caesar\, the conspiracy drama that made the Ides
  of March infamous\, so Brutus could be anyone. A one-night-only event\, p
 erformed with the company's usual table seating and food and drink service
  during the show.
GEO:33.768171;-84.3851523
LAST-MODIFIED:20260714T161552Z
LOCATION:Shakespeare Tavern Playhouse\, 499 Peachtree St NE
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://www.shakespearetavern.com/on-stage/company/shakespeare-out-of-
 a-hat-julius-caesar-on-the-ides-of-march
